Business Brief -- Automatic Data Processing Inc.:
   Firm's Earnings Rose 14%
   In Fiscal Second Quarter
The computer services company, based in Roseland, N.J.,
said second-quarter net income grew to $60.4 million, or 44
cents a share, from $53.2 million, or 39 cents a share.
Revenue rose 5.7% to $449.3 million from $425.1 million. Mr.
Weston said the brokerage transaction services, which
accounted for 20% of revenue, were helped by the recovery in
the securities industry. In addition, he said the company has
improved its client retention rate for payroll-processing
services.
   First-half net rose 12% to $106.1 million, or 77 cents a
share, from $95 million, or 67 cents a share. Revenue rose
4.6% to $878.4 million from $839.4 million.
   Separately, Automatic Data Processing said it acquired
Autonom Computer Beteiligungs G.m.b.H., a provider of
computer services to car dealer networks in Germany with
annual revenue of $20 million. Terms weren't disclosed.